! Pawn hunting. Black cannot win with just a bishop advantage - he has to break the pawn formation and find a way to get a pawn advantage and eventually promote the pawn. This move will do it. It helps that white's two rooks are on the far side of the board where they are far removed from defending the ruined king-side pawns.

And now it's a lock. Best for white would be Kf2 to stop the advance of black's passed e pawn, but then black just advances the g and h pawns for the win. The lone king cannot stop all three passed pawns, and white cannot force his queen-side pawns to break through.
